            }
        },
        "failed": false,
        "path": "test.log",
        "state": "absent"
    }


Above will the value stored in 'sriov_config_remove_result'. We are checking for the value the element "changed" to be true. And ansible generates the "changed" element as boolean by default. Casting to bool (|bool) is required only when the expected value is string, like "true", "yes", 1. Since this value is already boolean, there is no need for casting. 

This method of checking the bool value on when condition is also a documented way in ansible.
https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/2.7/user_guide/playbooks_conditionals.html#the-when-statement

